Edition:
Quote: On 12 February 1858, Stafford laid before the Executive Council a memorandum by the Ministers  on the state of affairs in Taranaki. <i>Ibid.</i> 132 It was noticeable that, whereas the [Taranaki] Provincial Council wanted Maori owners to be enabled to sell.. the Government implied that a majority wanted to sell. Ibid. 139 The Governor hitherto had seemed to understand that Maori land tenure was communal, as he had emphasized in June 1858 when refusing the Taranaki Provincial Council's petition that he compel a division of the common land.
